    "code": "012", 
    "data": "First Recite 8 rak’ats prayer (in units of 2 rak’ats each) with the intention of reciting the Naafelah of Namaaz-e-Shab. In the first rak’at, after surah Hamd recite surah Tawheed once and in the second rak’at after surah Hamd, recite surah Kaaferoon once.\nIn the remaining six rak’ats recite any short surah after surah Hamd. After completing 8 rak'ats of Naafelah recite Tasbih of Faatemah Zahra (s.a.). Thereafter recite 2 rak’ats ‘Namaaz-e-Shaf’. In the first rakat after surah Hamd recite surah Tawheed once. In the second rak’at after surah Hamd recite surah Falaq once.\nAfter ‘Namaaz-e-Shaf’ recite the following dua:\nاِلٰہِی تَعَرَّضَ لَکَ فِیْ ھٰذَا اللَّیْلِ الْمُتَعَرِّضُوْنَ \nELAAHEE TA-A’RRAZA LAKA FEE HAAZAL LAYLIL MOTA-A’RREZOON \nO Allah! Tonight, the seekers of favors, restless and eager, present themselves to You,\nوَ قَصَدَکَ الْقَاصِدُوْنَ \nWA QASADAKA FEEHIL QAASEDOON \nthe determined aspirers have You in mind,\nوَ اَمَّلَ فَضْلَکَ وَ مَعْرُوْفَکَ الطَّالِبُوْنَ \nWA AMMALA FAZLAKA WA MA’ROOFAQAT TAALEBOON \nand those who make requests look long and attentively at Your obligingness and kindness.\nوَ لَکَ فِیْ ھٰذَا اللَّیْلِ نَفَحَاتٌ وَ جَوَآئِزُ\nWA LAKA FEE HAAZAL LAYLE NAFAHAATUN \nYou, at this night, give gifts, bounties beyond measure,\nوَ عَطَایَا وَ مَوَاھِبُ \nWA JAWAAA-EZO WA A’TAAYAA WA MAWAAHEBO \nfree donations, and favors\nتَمُنُّ بِھَا عَلٰی مَنْ تَشَاءُ مِنْ عِبَادِکَ \nTAMUNNO BEHAA A’LAA MAN TASHAAA-O MIN E’BAADEKA \nto those whom You will from among Your servants when they make a request,\nوَ تَمْنَعُھَا مَنْ لَّمْ تَسْبِقُ لَہُ الْعِنَایَۃُ مِنْکَ \nWA TAMNA-O’HAA MAN LAM TASBEQO LAHUL E’NAAYATO MINKA \nand You say no to those who do not try to get in advance (i.e. remain behind) for obtaining the bounties from You.\nوَ ھَا اَنَاذَا عُبَیْدُکَ الْفَقِیْرُ اِلَیْکَ \nWA HAA ANAA ZAA O’BAIDOKAL FAQEERO ELAYKAL \nI, a modest needy bondman,\nالْمُؤَمِّلُ فَضْلَکَ وَ مَعْرُوْفَکَ \nMO-AMMELO FAZLAKA WA MA’ROOFAKA \nam hopeful of Your obligingness and kindness.\nفَاِنْ کُنْتَ یَا مَوْلَایَ \nFA-IN KUNTA YAA MAWLAAYA \nIndeed, if You, O My Master, \nتَفَضَّلْتَ فِیْ ھٰذِہٖ اللَّیْلَۃِ \nTAFAZZALTA FEE HAAZEHIL LAYLATE \nbestows a favor on any one, at this night, \nعَلٰیٓ اَحَدٍ مِّنْ خَلْقِکَ \nA’LAA AHADIM MIN KHALQEKA \nfrom among Your created beings,\nوَعُدْتَ عَلَیْہِ بِعَآئِدَۃٍ مِّنْ عَطْفِکَ \nWA U’DTA A’LAYHE BE-A’AEDATIM MIN A’TFEKA \nand multiply profits and gains for him out of Your love and affection,\nفَصَلِّ عَلٰی مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ اٰلِ مُحَمّدٍ \nFA-SALLE A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADENIT \nplease send blessings to Muhammad and the Household of Muhammad:\nالطَّیِّبِیْنَ الطَّاھِرِیْنَ \nTAYYEBEENAT TAAHEREENAL \nthe pure, the immaculate, \nالْخَّیِّرِیْنَ الْفَاضِلِیْنَ \nKHAYYEREE-NAL FAAZELEENA \nthe virtuous, and the righteous,\nوَجُدْ عَلَیَّ بِطَولِکَ وَ مَعْرُوْفِکَ \nWA JUD A’LAYYA BE-TAWLEYA WA MA’ROOFEKA \nand then give me abundantly on account of Your liberality and obligingness,\nیَا رَبَّ الْعَالَمِیْنَ \nYAA RABBAL A’ALAMEENA \nO Lord of the worlds!\nوَ صَلَّی اللّٰہُ عَلٰی مُحَمَّدٍ خَاتَمِ النَّبِیِّیْنَ \nWA SALLAL LAAHO A’LAA MOHAMMADIN KHAATAMIN NABIYYEENA \nMay Allah send blessings to Muhammad, the seal of the Prophets,\nوَ اٰلِہِ الطَّاھِرِیْنَ \nWA AALEHIT TAAHEREENA \nand upon his Household, the immaculate,\nوَ سَلَّمَ تَسْلِیْمًا \nWA SALLAMA TASLEEMAA \nand may He exalt them very much.\nاِنَّ اللّٰہَ حَمِیْدٌ مَجِیْدٌ \nINNAL LAAH HAMEEDUM MAJEED \nVerily, Allah is worthy of all praise, full of all glory.\nاَللَّھُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَدْعُوْکَ کَمَآ اَمَرْتَ \nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AD-O’OKA KAMAA AMARTA \nO Allah, I am praying You as You ordered me to do;\nفَاسْتَجِبْ لِیْ کَمَا وَعَدْتَ \nFAS-TAJBI LEE KAMAA WA-A’DTA \nso, (please) respond to me as You promised.\nاِنَّکَ لَا تُخْلِفُ الْمِیْعَادَ.\nINNAKA LAA TUKHLEFUL MEE-A’AD.\nVerily, You never break Your promise.\nAfter this recite one rak’at Namaaz-e-watr, in which, after surah Hamd, recite surah Tawheed, surah Falaq and surah Naas once each. Then raise your hands and recite the following Dua in Qunoot:\nلَا اِلٰہَ اِلَّا اللّٰہُ الْحَلِیْمُ الْکَرِیْمُ \nLAA ELAAHA ILAL LAAHUL HALEEMUL KAREEM\nThere is none worth worshipping but Allah Who is Forbearing and Generous\nلَا اِلٰہَ اِلَّا اللّٰہُ الْعَلِیُّ الْعَظِیْمُ \nLAA ELAAHA ILAL LAAHUL A’LIYYUL A’ZEEM\nThere is none worth worshipping but Allah Who is Most High and Great\nسُبْحَانَ اللّٰہِ رَبِّ السَّمٰوٰتِ السَّبْعِ \nSUBHAANAL LAAHE RABBIS SAMAAWAATIS SAB-E’ \nGlory be to Allah, Who is the Sustainer of the seven heavens \nوَ رَبِّ الْاَرَضِیْنَ السَّبْعِ \nWA RABBUL ARZEENAS SAB-E’ \nand of the seven earth\nوَ مَا فِیْھِنَّ وَ مَا بَیْنَھُنَّ \nWA MAA FEEHINNA WA MAA BAYNAHUNNA \nin them, and between them,\nوَ مَا فَوْقَھُنَّ وَ مَا تَحْتَحُنَّ \nWA MAA FAWQAHUNNA WA MAA TAHTAHUNNA \nabove them, beneath them\nوَ ھُوَ رَبُّ الْعَرْشِ الْعَظِیْمِ \nWA HOWA RABBUL A’RSHIL A’ZEEM \nAnd Who is the Lord of the great ‘Arsh (Divine Center of Authority & Power)\nوَ سَلَامٌ عَلٰی الْمُرْسَلِیْنَ \nWA SALAAMUN A’LAL MURSALEEN \nAnd peace be on the apostles. \nوَ الْحَمْدُ لِلّٰہِ رَبِّ الْعَالَمِیْنَ \nWAL HAMDO LILLAAHE RABBIL A’ALAMEEN \nAnd all praise for Allah, the Lord of the worlds.\nیَا اللّٰہُ الَّذِیْ لَیْسَ کَمِثْلِہٖ شَیْءٌ \nYAA ALLAAHUL LAZEE LAYSA KAMISLEHI SHAYUN \nO Allah! The One nothing is like Him\nوَ ھُوَ السَّمِیْعُ الْبَصِیْرُ \nWA HOWAS SAMEE-U’L BASEER \nand He is the Hearing, the Seeing.\nوَ صَلِّ عَلٰی مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ آلِ مُحَمَّدٍ.\nWA SALLE A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMAD.\nAnd blessings be upon Muhammad and the progeny of Muhammad.\nRecite the following 70 or 100 times:\nاَسْتَغْفِرُ اللّٰہَ رَبِّیْ وَ اَتُوْبُ اِلَیْہِ.\nRecite the following 7 times:\nاَسْتَغْفِرُ اللّٰہَ الَّذِیْ لَا اِلٰہَ اِلَّا ھُوَ الْحَیُّ القَیُّوْمُ بِجَمِیْعِ ظُلْمِیْ وَ جُرْمِیْ وَ اِسْرَافِیْ عَلٰی نَفْسِیْ وَ اَتُوْبُ اِلَیْہِ.\nRecite 7 times:\nھٰذَا مَقَامُ الْعَائِذِ بِکَ مِنَ النَّارِ.\nRecite the following 300 times:\nاَلْعَفْوَ\nThen say:\nرَبِّ اغْفِرْ لِيْ وَ ارْحَمْنِيْ وَ تُبْ عَلَيَّ\nRABBIGH FIR LEE WAR HAMNEE WA TUB A’LAYYA\nO my Lord, (please) forgive me, have mercy upon me, and accept my repentance,\nاِنَّكَ اَنْتَ التَّوَّابُ الْغَفُوْرُ الرَّحِيْمُ\nINNAKA ANTAT TAWWABUL GHAFOORUR RAHEEMO\nfor You are surely the Oft-Returning, the All-forgiving, and the All-merciful.\nMention names of 40 living or deceased believers one by one and say:\nاَللّٰھُمَّ اغفِرْ لِھٰذَا ...........Name\nThis dua is to be recited after Namaz-e-Shab:\nبِسْمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِيْمِ.\nاُنَاجِیْکَ یَا مَوْجُوْدًا فِیْ کُلِّ مَکَانٍ \nONAAJEEKA YAA MAWJOODAN FEE KULLE MAKAANIN \nO One who is present everywhere. \nلَعَلَّکَ تَسْمَعُ نِدَآئِیْ \nLA-A’LLAKA TASMA-O NEDAAA-EE \nI beseech You (and) hoping that You will listen to my voice, \nفَقَدْ عَظُمَ جُرْمِیْ وَ قَلَّ حَیَآئِیْ \nFAQAD A’ZOMA JURMEE WA QALLA HAYAA-EE \nbecause surely, my sin is big and my feeling of guilt has lessened.\nمَوْلَایَ یَا مَوْلَایَ اَیَّ الْاَھْوَالِ اَتَذَکَّرُ وَ اَیَّھَا اَنْسٰی \nMAWLAAYA YAA MAWLAAYA AYYAL AHWAALE ATAZAKKARO WA AYYAHA ANSAA \nMy Lord, My Lord! How many fear do I recount, how many fear do I forget. \nوَ لَوْ لَمْ یَکُنْ اِلاَّ الْمَوْتُ لَکَفٰی \nWA LAW LAM YAKUN ILLAL MAWTO LAKAFAA \nIt there was no fear except fear of death, that fear was enough. \nکَیْفَ وَمَا بَعْدَ الْمَوْتِ اَعْظَمُ وَ اَدْھٰی \nKAYFA WA MAA BA’DAL MAWTE A-A’ZAMO WA ADHAA \nThe fear of after death is very big and very severe.\nمَولاَیَ یَا مَوْلاَیَ حَتّٰی مَتٰی وَ اِلٰي مَتٰي \nMAWLAAYA YAA MAWLAAYA HATTAA MATAA WA ELAA MATAA \nMy Master and My Lord! How many times should I say that I want You should be pleased with me. \nاَقُوْلُ لَکَ الْعُتْبٰی مَرَّۃً بَعْدَ اُخْرٰی \nAQOOLO LAKAL UTBAA MARRATAN BA’DA UKHRAA \nI say this again and again. \nثُمَّ لاَ تَجِدُ عِنْدِیْ صِدْقًا وَ لاَ وَفَآءً \nSUMMA LAA TAJEDO I’NDEE SIDQAN WA LAA WAFAAA-AN \nEven then, You do not get truth and acceptance of faithfulness from me! \nفَیَاغَوْثَاہُ ثُمَّ وَاغَوْثَاہُ بِکَ \nFA-YAA GHAWSAA-HO SUMMA WAA GHAWSAA-HO BEKA \nSo give me protection. There is no protection save from You. \nیَا اَللّٰہُ مِنْ ھَوًی قَدْ غَلَبَنِیْ \nYAA ALLAAHO MIN HAWAN QAD GHALABANEE \nO Allah, safeguard me from the desires of the soul which have overpowered me, \nوَ مِنْ عَدُوٍّ قَدِ اسْتَکْلَبَ عَلَیَّ \nWA MIN A’DUWWIN QADIS TAKLABA A’LAYYA \nsafeguard me from the enemy who is ready to attack me, \nوَ مِنْ دُنْیَا قَدْ تَزَیَّنَتْ لِیْ \nWA MIN DUNYAA QAD TAZAYYANAT LEE \nprotect me from the evils of the world \nوَ مِنْ نَفْسٍ اَمَّارَۃٍ بِالسُّوٓءِ اِلاَّ مَا رَحِمَ رَبِّیْ \nWA MIN NAFSIN AMMAARATIN BIS-SOOO-E ILLAA MAA RAHEMA RABBEE \nand the evil of the soul which has disobeyed me. Except that You have mercy on me.\nمَوْلاَیَ یَا مَوْلاَیَ اِنْ کُنْتَ رَحِمْتَ مِثْلِی فَارْحَمْنِیْ \nMAWLAAYA YAA MAWLAAYA IN KUNTA RAHIMTA MISLEE FARHAMNEE \nMy Lord, My Lord! if You have shown Mercy on someone like me, then have mercy on me. \nوَ اِنْ کُنْتَ قَبِلْتَ مِثْلِیْ فَاقْبَلْنِیْ \nWA IN KUNTA QABILTA MISLEE FAQBALNEE \nIf you have accepted repentance of someone like me, then forgive me. \nیَا قَبِلَ السَّحَرَۃِ اِقْبَلْنِیْ \nYAA KAABELAS-SAHARATE IQBALNEE \nO Acceptor of morning Dua. Accept my Dua.\nیَا مَنْ لَمْ اَزَلْ اَتَعَرَّفُ مِنْہُ الْحُسْنٰی \nYAA MAN LAM AZAL ATA-A’RRAFO MINHUL HUSNAA \nO whom I always consider goodness. \nیَا مَنْ یُغَذِّیْنِیْ بِالنِّعَمِ صَبَاحًا وَ مَسَآءً \nYAA MAN YOGAZZEENEE BIN NEA’ME SABAAHAN WA MASAAHAN \nO who provides me sustenance morning and evening. \nاِرْحَمْنِیْ یَوْمَ اٰتِیْکَ فَرْدًا شَاخِصًا اِلَیْکَ بَصَرِیْ \nIRHAMNEE YAWMAA AATEEKA FARDAN SHAAKHESAN ELAYKA BASAREE \nHave mercy on me on the day when I come to You alone, \nمُقَلَّدًا عَمَلِیْ قَدْ تَبَرَّءَ جَمِیْعُ الْخَلْقِ مِنِّیْ \nMOQALLADAN A’MALEE QAD TABARRA-A JAMEE-U’L KHALQE MINNEE \nmy deeds hanging around my neck, at a time when everyone will be disgusted with me, \nنَعَمْ وَ اَبِیْ وَ اُمِّیْ وَ مَنْ کَانَ لَہٗ کَدِّیْ وَ سَعْیِیْ \nNA-A’M WA ABEE WA UMMEE WA MAN KAANA LAHU QADDEE WA SA’YEE \nso much so that even my father and mother for whom I had tried and worked (they also will be disgusted with me)\nفَاِنْ لَمْ تَرْحَمْنِیْ فَمَنْ یَرْحَمُنِیْ \nFA-IN LAM TARHAMNEE FA-MAN YARHAMONEE \nSo (that day) if You will not show mercy on me, who will show mercy on me? \nوَ مَنْ یُوْنِسُ فِیْ الْقَبْرِ وَحْشَتِیْ \nWA MAN YOONESO FIL QABRE WAHSHATEE \nWho will be my well-wisher in the loneliness of the grave? \nوَ مَنْ یُنْطِقُ لِسَانِیْ اِذَا خَلَوْتُ بِعَمَلِیْ وَ سَاءَلْتَنِیْ \nWA MAN YUNTEQO LESAANEE EZAA KHALAWTO BE-A’MALEE WA SAA-ALTANEE \nWho will activate my tongue (give me strength of speak), when I will be coming with my deeds and You will ask me about my life \nعَمَّا اَنْتَ اَعْلَمُ بِہٖ مِنِّیْ \nA’MMAA ANTA A-A’LAMO BEHI MINNEE\nwith which You are more familiar.\nفَاِنْ قُلْتُ نَعَمْ فَاَیْنَ الْمَحْرَبُ مِنْ عَدْلِکَ \nFA-IN QULTO NA-A’M FA-AYNAL MAHRABO MIN A’DLEKA \nSo, if I accept my deeds, where is the place to run away from Your Justice. \nوَ اِنْ قُلْتُ لَمْ اَفْعَلْ قُلْتَ اَلَمْ اَکُنِ الشَّاھِدَ عَلَیْکَ \nWA IN QULTO LAM AF-A’L QULTA ALAM AKANISH SHAAHEDA A’LAYKA \nIf I deny me deeds, You will say ‘Was I not watching your deeds?’\nفَعَفْوُکَ عَفْوُکَ یَا مَوْلاَیَ قَبْلَ سَرَابِیْلِ الْقَطِرَانِ \nFA-A’FWOKA A’FWOK YAA MAWLAAYA QABLA SARAABEELIL QATERAANE \nSo, forgive me, O my Lord, my Master. Forgive me before I wear the dress of Hell. \nعَفْوُکَ عَفْوُکَ یَا مَوْلاَیَ قَبْلَ جَھَنَّمَ وَ النِّیْرَانِ \nA’FWOKA A’FWOK YAA MAWLAAYA QABLA JAHANNAMA WAN NEERAANE \nO my Lord, forgive me before the Hell and Fire,\nعَفْوُکَ عَفْوُکَ یَا مَوْلاَیَ قَبْلَ اَنْ تُغَلَّ الْاَیْدِیْ اِلٰی الْاَعْنَاقِ \nA’FWOKA A’FWOK YAA MAWLAAYA QABLA AN TOGHALLAL AYDEE ELAL A-A’NAAKE \nO my Lord, forgive me before my hands are tied towards my neck, \nیَا اَرْحَمَ الرَّاحِمِیْنَ وَ خَیْرَ الْغَافِرِیْنَ.\nYAA ARHAMAR RAAHEMEEN WA KHAYRAL GHAAFEREEN.\nO the most Merciful and the most Benevolent.", 
    "title": "Namaz e Shab"
}